I used to belong to an unofficial natural history group in the Eastern Province. Every few weeks we'd drive up the Dammam-Riyadh Expressway and sometimes drive 1000km off road in the Dahna and camp. my fave region near Dhahran is Hamra Judah - I camped there a lot. I have hundreds of GPS coords from my travels back in the 90s between the Abandoned village Qaryat As Sufla on the old Tapline Road, the Mastodon Bones in the cave roof near there, Shark tooth Wadi, all sorts of cool exploring info which we need to give back to the Saudis themselves now.
